<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="330" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="7.[812,1422,1586,1991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1044,1659,1683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Examined material.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1169,1659,1683]" name="Bolivia" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">BOLIVIA</collectingCountry>
; Province of Ñuflo de Chávez of 
<collectingRegion box="[930,1191,1693,1717]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Santa Cruz Department</collectingRegion>
; Centro “Chiquitos”; camera stations 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 13 (
<tableCitation box="[1280,1357,1726,1750]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[168,222,162,182]" captionText="Table 1. Camera stations, habitat type, and geogrpahic coordinates." pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Table 1</tableCitation>
); first capture on 
<date box="[929,1053,1760,1785]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" value="2017-05-01">1 May 2017</date>
; secondary forest patch in pastureland, primary forest, and border of pastureland to forest. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,974,1832,1856]" pageId="7" pageNumber="330">Identification.</emphasis>
The melero or Tayra is a medium-sized mustelid (
<quantity box="[925,1007,1866,1891]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="330" unit="kg" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7 kg</quantity>
), with a long body and neck, short limbs, and a long, hairy tail. The body is dark brown, except for the head and neck, which is lighter brown, and the throat, which has a whitish spot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
